# Session Log Rule

Always read `.cursor/rules/session-log.md` before responding.

When a meaningful unit of work is completed:

- Move "Current Session" → "Previous Session"
- Write a new "Current Session" with:
  - What I did (1–2 bullets)
  - Why it matters (1 bullet)
  - Next step (1 bullet)

Constraints:

- Keep entries concise
- Max ~300 characters per section
- Do not add additional sections
- Overwrite old content, do not append history

Only update when:

- the user says "checkpoint"
- or a multi-step task is completed
